              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4863319291238370694">The way Djebar grapples with her French/Algerian identity in this book shows itself through the form. Carefully crafted in all its parts - she plays with ways of historicizing and organizing information. One just has to remember that some of the narrative is, in the end, overwhelmingly in her perspective. Still a lovely way to humanize the experience of the French conquest of Algeria and the National Liberation movement.</span>

