    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2677673805" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2677673805" />
    <a title="Caterina Pierre" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/11371828-caterina-pierre"><img alt="Caterina Pierre" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1343522761p2/11371828.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2677673805?book_show_action=true">Feb 24, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Caterina Pierre" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Caterina Pierre" href="/user/show/11371828-caterina-pierre">Caterina Pierre</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9782253151272" href="/book/show/74706.L_Amour_la_fantasia">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2677673805" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7144677838051995112">I had the privilege of reading this book as part of a Club de Lecture with 7 other students and a professional literature teacher. It’s a difficult book to read for a non-native French speaker because one might need a little background in French Colonial history to truly grasp the totality of the stories presented in it. While the book is a novel, it does not have a linear plot. Instead it is a compilation of vignettes, ranging from retelling of events during the French-Algerian War and the Alge</span>
  <span id="freeText7144677838051995112" style="display:none">I had the privilege of reading this book as part of a Club de Lecture with 7 other students and a professional literature teacher. It’s a difficult book to read for a non-native French speaker because one might need a little background in French Colonial history to truly grasp the totality of the stories presented in it. While the book is a novel, it does not have a linear plot. Instead it is a compilation of vignettes, ranging from retelling of events during the French-Algerian War and the Algerian War for Independence through women’s voices and stories; memories of the narrator’s youth in France; and the voices of the women whom the narrator has interviewed or women’s stories that she has researched and collected. It’s sort of safe to assume the narrator is Djebar, though it’s only inferred and not explicitly stated in the book. Ultimately this is a text in which Djebar reclaims a space for the voices of the women harmed through these colonial wars. The fact that she wrote the book in the language of the colonizers both complicates it and allows the women’s stories to be known to a wider audience. The narrator grapples with the issue of language throughout the book. Clearly it is a masterwork of post-colonial feminist writing.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7144677838051995112" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

