        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4114091400" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5453012619172720673">In this stunning novel, Assia Djebar combines the history of her country, Algeria, with insidents from the life of a young girl which was taken from the story about French conquest in 1830 to the War of Liberation of the 1950s. The young girl, growing up in the old Roman seaside town of Cherchel, discerns her life in contrast to her French family neighbors, and misses the things more than that the laws and traditions permits her to experience. She escapes from her families cloistered life in ord</span>
  <span id="freeText5453012619172720673" style="display:none">In this stunning novel, Assia Djebar combines the history of her country, Algeria, with insidents from the life of a young girl which was taken from the story about French conquest in 1830 to the War of Liberation of the 1950s. The young girl, growing up in the old Roman seaside town of Cherchel, discerns her life in contrast to her French family neighbors, and misses the things more than that the laws and traditions permits her to experience. She escapes from her families cloistered life in order to join her brother in the maquis’s flight against French domination. Djebar elucidates her own countries and Algeria’s girl’s and women’s double effort for independence<br /><br />- ilay</span>
